 Photo taken with a mobile phone shows the winter scenery of Zhegu lake in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, Dec. 4, 2021. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing) SHANNAN, Dec. 5 (Xinhua) -- Zhegu lake is located in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, with an area of about 70 square kilometers and an average water depth of about 20 meters. The water source of Zhegu lake nourishes the grassland, where many wild animals and other domestic animals enjoy natural pastures and coexist harmoniously with the natural environment. Enjoy the winter scenery of Zhegu lake.  Photo taken with a mobile phone shows the winter scenery of Zhegu lake in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, Dec. 4, 2021. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing)  Photo taken with a mobile phone shows the winter scenery of Zhegu lake in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, Dec. 4, 2021. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing)  Photo taken with a mobile phone shows the winter scenery of Zhegu lake in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, Dec. 4, 2021. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing)  Photo taken on Dec. 4, 2021 shows Kiangs (Equus kiang) at Zhegu grassland in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing)  Photo taken with a mobile phone shows the winter scenery of Zhegu lake in Shannan City, southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, Dec. 4, 2021. (Xinhua/Shen Hongbing)â– 